  "name": "Moonleaf Tincture",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubFantasy0001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A pale silver tincture distilled from leaves harvested only on cloudless nights. Bards swear by it; sober courts forbid it. The taste is faintly metallic and the aftertaste hums in the back of the throat.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour you speak in unintended cadences and have advantage on Charisma (Persuasion) checks made to convince listeners of small or beautiful things.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Moonleaf Tincture (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Moonleaf Tincture.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Intelligence saving throws (your thoughts wander toward verses you can't quite finish).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 2.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(2 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 1) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Tincture Dropper.</em></p>"
    },
